==Guaranteed Red Cabbage==
If the ''Guarantee Year 1 Completable'' [[Options|advanced option]] was enabled when creating the save, the traveling cart is guaranteed to sell [[Red Cabbage Seeds]] at least once in the first year, between spring 7 in [[Cindersap Forest]] (the cart's second visit) and winter 16 at the [[Night Market]] (the cart's 30th visit). The day is selected at random when the save is created. The guarantee only applies on that single day, even if the player doesn't check the cart or buy the seeds on that day.<ref name="guaranteeseeds" />

==External Links==
Players with access to their [[Saves|saved game files]] may find the "Stardew Predictor" utility helpful for predicting which items the Traveling Cart will offer each week, and during the [[Night Market]].  The utility is located at https://mouseypounds.github.io/stardew-predictor/.

==Bugs==
* For the Android and iOS version of the game, after buying something from the cart and closing and reopening the shop menu, the item can be purchased again. This can be repeated indefinitely.

==References==
<references>
<ref name="guaranteeseeds">The game code initializes <samp>Game1.netWorldState.Value.VisitsUntilY1Guarantee</samp> in <samp>Game1::loadForNewGame</samp>, then decrements it for each traveling cart visit. Red Cabbage Seeds are guaranteed when the value reaches zero, after which it's decremented to -1 and no longer applies.</ref>
<ref name="teaset25">See <samp>Content\Data\Shops.xnb</samp>. In the Traveler's section, the condition for the Tea Set to appear is <samp>YEAR 25, SYNCED_RANDOM day teaset .05</samp>.</ref>
</references>

